Prof. Steven (Shichang) Gao, IEEE Fellow

University of Kent

Research Interests:

Antennas, RF/microwave/millimetre-wave circuits and RF front ends, mobile communication systems, satellite communications, inter-satellite links, wireless power transfer, UWB radars, GNSS reflectometry, synthetic-aperture radars, electromagnetic modelling and small satellites

Homepage:

https://www.kent.ac.uk/engineering-digital-arts/people/670/gao-steven#professional



Prof. Guy Vandenbosch, IEEE Fellow

Katholieke Universiteit Leuven

Research Interests:

Electromagnetic theory, computational electromagnetics, planar antennas and circuits, nano electromagnetics, EM radiation, EMC, and bioelectromagnetics.

Homepage:

https://www.esat.kuleuven.be/telemic/People-of-telemic/00005450

 

Prof. Ronan Sauleau, IEEE Fellow

Université de Rennes 1

Research Interests:

Numerical modeling, millimeter-wave printed and reconfigurable antennas, substrate integrated waveguide antennas, lens-based focusing devices, periodic and non-periodic structures, and biological effects of millimeter waves.

